<% content_for(:title, 'Home') %>
<div class = "blogApp">
  <div class="jumbotron">
    <h3 align='center'>Welcome to my blog!</h3>
    <p>Hi! My name is Aaron Rohrbacher, and I'm Portland's 22nd-or-so newest junior web developer. I've built this simple blog in Ruby on Rails, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, and some JavaScript and jQuery. I intend to be discussing some weird little things I've come across while continuing my programming career. May they help you immensely, or annoy the s#!+ out of you! <em>Either way, please feel free to leave a comment!</em></p>
  </div>
  <hr>
  <div class="row">
    <% @posts.each do |post| %>
      <div class = "col-md-4">
        <div class = "card cardFront proxima">
          <div class = "heading proxima">
            <h2 class = 'proxima'><%= link_to post.title, post_path(post) %></h2>
            <hr>
          </div>
          <p><em><%= post.created_at.in_time_zone("Pacific Time (US & Canada)").strftime('%m/%d/%Y')%></em></p>
            <p><strong><%= post.description %></strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>


